    "body": "<!-- devin-review-comment {\"id\": \"BUG_pr-review-job-7fb63ea0faef423bbf98674b4bd79ae8_0001\", \"file_path\": \"lib/api-client.ts\", \"start_line\": 27, \"end_line\": 29, \"side\": \"RIGHT\"} -->\n\n🔴 **`fetchApi` silently returns `null` typed as `T` when a successful response has a non-JSON body**\n\nWhen the HTTP response is successful (2xx) but the body cannot be parsed as JSON (e.g., 204 No Content, or a plain text response), the `try/catch` block at lines 25-29 catches the parse error and sets `data = null`. The `!response.ok` check at line 31 passes since the response IS ok, so the function proceeds to line 39 and returns `null as T`.\n\n<details>\n<summary>Root Cause and Impact</summary>\n\nThe function signature `Promise<T>` guarantees a non-null `T` to callers, but `null` can actually be returned. Any caller that destructures or accesses properties on the result will get a runtime `TypeError`:\n\n```ts\nconst user = await fetchApi<{ name: string }>('/api/create-user', { method: 'POST', body: ... });\nconsole.log(user.name); // TypeError: Cannot read properties of null\n```\n\nThis would occur for any API endpoint that returns a 2xx status with an empty or non-JSON body. The fix should either throw an error when JSON parsing fails on a successful response, or change the return type to `T | null`.\n\n</details>\n\n```suggestion\n    } catch (error) {\n        if (response.ok) {\n            throw new ApiError(response.status, 'Yanıt JSON olarak ayrıştırılamadı');\n        }\n        data = null;\n    }\n```\n\n<!-- devin-review-badge-begin -->\n<a href=\"https://app.devin.ai/review/celaluysl/agencycrm/pull/3\" target=\"_blank\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://static.devin.ai/assets/gh-open-in-devin-review-dark.svg?v=1\">\n    <img src=\"https://static.devin.ai/assets/gh-open-in-devin-review-light.svg?v=1\" alt=\"Open in Devin Review\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n<!-- devin-review-badge-end -->\n\n---\