    "body": "<!-- devin-review-comment {\"id\": \"ANALYSIS_pr-review-job-7fb63ea0faef423bbf98674b4bd79ae8_0001\", \"file_path\": \"lib/utils.ts\", \"start_line\": 19, \"end_line\": 21, \"side\": \"RIGHT\"} -->\n\n🚩 **`formatDate` will throw on invalid date strings rather than returning a fallback**\n\nThe `formatDate` function at `lib/utils.ts:19-21` guards against `null` and `undefined` but not against invalid date strings. If a malformed string like `\"not-a-date\"` is passed, `new Date(\"not-a-date\")` produces an `Invalid Date` object, and `format()` from date-fns v4 will throw a `RangeError`. Since the function already returns `\"-\"` as a fallback for missing values, it seems like the intent is graceful degradation — but invalid strings won't get that treatment. This isn't flagged as a bug because the function isn't consumed yet and the type signature accepting `string` may be intended for only well-formed ISO date strings from Supabase. However, if this utility is used with user input or untrusted data, it will crash.\n\n<!-- devin-review-badge-begin -->\n<a href=\"https://app.devin.ai/review/celaluysl/agencycrm/pull/3\" target=\"_blank\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://static.devin.ai/assets/gh-open-in-devin-review-dark.svg?v=1\">\n    <img src=\"https://static.devin.ai/assets/gh-open-in-devin-review-light.svg?v=1\" alt=\"Open in Devin Review\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n<!-- devin-review-badge-end -->\n\n---\n*Was this helpful? React with 👍 or 👎 to provide feedback.*",
